set default deny

interface mgmt = "ens3"
interface wan = "wan0"
interface lan = "lan0"
interface wg = "wg0"

table <wg_peers> { 10.8.0.0/24 }
table <wg_admins> { 10.8.0.10, 10.8.0.11 }
table <wg_guests> { 10.8.0.100, 10.8.0.101 }
table <lan_nets> { 10.0.0.0/24, 10.20.0.0/24 }
table <db_hosts> { 10.20.0.10, 10.20.0.11 }
table <dns_resolvers> { 10.0.0.53, 1.1.1.1, 9.9.9.9 }

queue bulk on wan bandwidth 200mbit
queue interactive on wan bandwidth 20mbit parent bulk

pass in on mgmt proto tcp from any to any port 22 keep state
pass out on mgmt from any to any keep state

pass in log on wan proto udp from any to any port 51820 keep state

nat on wan from <wg_peers> to any -> wan

pass in on wg proto udp from <wg_peers> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue interactive
pass in on wg proto tcp from <wg_peers> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue interactive

pass in log (user) on wg proto tcp from <wg_admins> to <lan_nets> port 22 keep state queue interactive
pass in log (user) on wg proto tcp from <wg_admins> to <lan_nets> port 443 keep state queue interactive
pass in log on wg proto tcp from <wg_admins> to <db_hosts> port 5432 keep state queue interactive
block in log (all) on wg from <wg_guests> to <lan_nets>
pass in on wg proto tcp from <wg_peers> to <lan_nets> port 443 keep state queue bulk

pass in on wg proto tcp from <wg_guests> to any port 80 keep state queue bulk
pass in on wg proto tcp from <wg_guests> to any port 443 keep state queue bulk
pass in on wg proto udp from <wg_guests> to <dns_resolvers> port 53 keep state queue interactive

block in log (user) on wg from <wg_peers> to <wg_peers>

pass out on wan proto udp from <wg_peers> to any port 53 keep state
pass out on wan proto tcp from <wg_peers> to any port 80 keep state queue bulk
pass out on wan proto tcp from <wg_peers> to any port 443 keep state queue bulk

block in log (all) on wan from any to any
block in log (all) on wg from any to any
block out log (user) on wan from any to any
